wiki.summary: "Celebrity" is IU's pre-release comeback single first announced in January 11, 2021. It is a cheerful and energetic pop song which will be part of her new studio album in almost four years. IU's comeback single was released on January 27, 2021 at 18:00 KST (UTC+9) in major online streaming platforms in Korea and worldwide. "Celebrity" was written by IU based on the experienced of a close friend who was scrutinised for being different. She wrote the things she want to tell her friend and it became a complete song. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: "Celebrity" is IU's pre-release comeback single first announced in January 11, 2021. It is a cheerful and energetic pop song which will be part of her new studio album in almost four years. IU's comeback single was released on January 27, 2021 at 18:00 KST (UTC+9) in major online streaming platforms in Korea and worldwide. "Celebrity" was written by IU based on the experienced of a close friend who was scrutinised for being different. She wrote the things she want to tell her friend and it became a complete song. The queen of pop also wrote the lyrics for everyone who feels odd that they too are a Celebrity. Global Top Tracks Chart history in LastFM: [*] Top 7 by 20:00 KST [*] Top 5 by 20:21 KST [*] Top 4 by 20:37 KST Achievements Aside from achieving Top 4 in the LastFM Global Top Tracks Chart two hours after release, the "Celebrity" music video in YouTube has already reached 2,829,136 views by 23:24 KST. It was also the fastest song to enter the MelOn 24Hits Top 10, making it to rank 1 in only two hours. By 21:00 KST, "Celebrity" broke the record for the fastest song to achieve a real-time all-kill since MelOn and FLO changed their algorithms. The pre-release single hit the Top 2 rank in MelOn All Time unique listeners in the first hour of release, garnering 156,720 unique listeners. Top 1 was IU's "Eight (f. SUGA)" which garnered 199,327 unique listeners. Read more on Last.fm. User-contributed text is available under the Creative Commons By-SA License; additional terms may apply.
